# Authority model

> **Reference** · for integrators · **read when** you need the exact "who may write what"

Who may write what. Write authority is **derived**: a role may write a zone iff it holds the capability that zone's `kind:` requires. The meaning of each capability and the rules around them live in [`zones.md`](zones.md) — this page is the projected table of current values.

## Lanes — the zone-kind ↔ capability bijection

Each zone-kind maps 1:1 to exactly one capability (ADR 0091).

| Zone `kind` | Required capability |
|-------------|---------------------|
<% lanes.each do |lane| -%>| `<%= lane["kind"] %>` | `<%= lane["capability"] %>` |
<% end -%>
